Diagram 3 (Correct)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Descending at 1 is a great move.
\par
\par As soon as this move is played, something about black looks strange.
\par \pard\nowidctlpar\qj If black plays at 2, it is perfect for white to throw-in with 3. Next, if black plays at \b\f1 A\b0\f0 , white plays at \b\f1 B\b0\f0 . Black is finished.
\par \pard
\par }
